  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title [Repealed.].
  content `1. [Repeal of Reg. XXVIII of 1802, s. 23] Rep., Act XIV of 1874.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347&sectionId=76453&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (76454)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Tahsildars empowered to sell property distrained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. The words “And it is hereby enacted that from the said day” were repealed by the Repealing Act, 1873 (XII of 1873).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347&sectionId=76454&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1**** All tahsildars within the territories`
  line `subject to the Presidency of Fort St. George shall be vested with the powers of Commissioners for the sale`
  line `of property distrained for arrears of rent or of revenue, and shall be subject to all rules and provisions to`
  line `which by any law or regulation such Commissioners are subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (76455)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Control of tahsildars in exercise of such power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347&sectionId=76455&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Provided always that in respect of the exercise`
  line `of those powers tahsildars shall be subject to the control and superintendence of the Collector, and shall`
  line `not be subject to the authority of the Zila Judge, except in the case of any judicial proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (76456)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Repealed..
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347&sectionId=76456&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `4. [Their liabilities in exercise of same power.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1891`
  line `(XII of 1891).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (76457)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Fees for selling property to be credited to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347&sectionId=76457&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Provided also that tahsildars shall not`
  line `be entitled to any fee or commission for selling such distrained property; but that all fees or commission`
  line `which may be now lawfully taken by Commissioners for the sale of such distrained property shall be`
  line `taken and carried to the account of Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (76458)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Delegation of tahsildars powers.`
  content `And it is herby enacted that tahsildars shall have authority, subject to the orders of the Collector, to delegate the powers vested in them by the second section of this Act to any public servants placed under their authority; and that the provisions of ^1[sections 3 and 5] of this Act shall apply to all public servants to whom those powers shall have so delegated in the same manner as they apply to tahsildars.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347&sectionId=76458&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_183907_1691478563347
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures in square brackets have been substituted for the words “the three last proceeding sections” by the`
  line `Amending Act, 1801 (XII of 1891). General Acts, Vol. IV.`
